Welcome to Dry Powder. I=E2=80=99m Bill Cohan.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

For a myriad of reasons, including the capitulation of media companies to l=
egal pressure from the Trump administration, we=E2=80=99ve stumbled headlon=
g into a veritable golden age for litigation and other intimidation tactics=
 against journalists and their publishers. Of course, it=E2=80=99s too earl=
y to say whether this era will culminate in sweeping changes to defamation =
law=E2=80=94e.g., the end of New
York Times v. Sullivan=E2=80=94or will instead turn out to be an anomalous =
historical blip, but in any case, New York Times business investigations ed=
itor David Enrich has written a new book, Murder the Truth, which is a most=
 fascinating and comprehensive chronicle of this new threat to journalism. =
I spoke to David for today=E2=80=99s issue, and dug into a few of the most =
germane cases that potentially foreshadow where this is all headed.

=C2=A0

But first=E2=80=A6

* More carried interest anxiety?: Yesterday, my partner Peter Hamby brillia=
ntly distilled ( https://puck.news/gavin-newsoms-podcast-is-serving-its-pur=
pose-attention/?utm_campaign=3DDry+Powder+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%283%2F12%2F25%29&u=
