9999997px;"><strong>A
Chilling Effect</strong></h3>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<table width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" role=
=3D"presentation" style=3D"mso-table-lspace:0pt;mso-table-rspace:0pt;word-b=
reak:break-word;"><tbody><tr><td style=3D"padding-bottom:32px;"><div style=
=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;Inter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;=
;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;line-height:150%;text-al=
ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;">Enrich=E2=80=99s book also traces how plaintiffs and their well-paid la=
wyers are moving closer
to challenging <em>Sullivan</em> at the Supreme Court. He told me that one =
of Libby Locke=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cpersonal goals=E2=80=9D is to persuade as=
 many people as possible that <em>New York Times v. Sullivan</em> was =E2=
=80=9Cwrongly decided,=E2=80=9D that it makes it too difficult to hold the =
media accountable for reputational damage, and =E2=80=9Cshould be overturne=
d.=E2=80=9D (Locke did not address this particular claim in her response to=
 me.)=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">She
wouldn=E2=80=99t be the only one. On Monday, <strong>Don Blankenship</stron=
g>, the former West Virginia coal executive who spent time in prison and th=
en tried his hand at politics, filed an amicus brief in support of casino m=
ogul<strong> Steve Wynn</strong>=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://email.puck.ne=
ws/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dWak9pTUZSbjhfQVdHVHRJaExp=
RT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucmV1dGVycy5jb20vbGVnYWwvY2FzaW5vLW1vZ3VsLXd=
5bm4tYXNrcy11cy1zdXByZW1lLWNvdXJ0LXJldmlzaXQtdGltZXMtdi1zdWxsaXZhbi1kZWZhbW=
F0aW9uLXJ1bGUtMjAyNS0wMi0wNy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPURyeStQb3dkZXIrLStTVUJTQ1JJQ=
kVSUyslMjgzJTJGMTIlMkYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9jb250ZW50PURyeStQb3dkZXIrLStTVUJT=
Q1JJQkVSUyslMjgzJTJGMTIlMkYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWxfYWN0aW9uXHU=
wMDI2dXRtX3NvdXJjZT1jdXN0b21lci5pb1x1MDAyNnV0bV90ZXJtPWY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZD=
EyYSIsImludGVybmFsIjoiZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6MjExODMwM30/6=
e2a33a33883d3a3145c419e7066aa23714ff36524823a0f3be117ddb71a04db" style=3D"t=
ext-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">legal efforts</a> to overturn <em>=
Sullivan</em>. =E2=80=9CWe live in a day
and age where the once noble profession of journalism has been hijacked by =
zealots using the flagships of American media to exhort their own personal =
and political biases and opinions to destroy hard earned reputations of pub=
lic figures,=E2=80=9D Blankenship wrote.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;marg=
in-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Enrich t=
old me he doesn=E2=80=99t think <em>Sullivan</em> is close to being overtur=
ned quite yet, but said he wouldn=E2=80=99t be surprised if the court
eventually made a ruling that would limit the =E2=80=9Cactual malice=E2=80=
=9D standard to public officials only, as opposed to private citizens who a=
re <em>public figures</em>, such as wealthy businesspeople. =E2=80=9CThat c=
ould have an enormous chilling effect on the ability of journalists, and th=
e public in general, to criticize or scrutinize the affairs of really rich =
people, who wield enormous amounts of influence and power in our society an=
d in our economy,=E2=80=9D he said.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bo=
ttom:0px;">
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Ironically, in recent we=
eks, Bill Ackman has found himself involved in a separate dispute with Clar=
e Locke, much to everyone=E2=80=99s amusement. Earlier this year, in the wa=
ke of the December 2024 murder of UnitedHealthcare C.E.O. <strong>Brian Tho=
mpson</strong>, the insurance giant hired Clare Locke to go after anyone wh=
o dared criticize the company for denying coverage to patients. In February=
, on X, Ackman reposted a note by a doctor
who claimed that UnitedHealthcare had denied care to one of her patients. H=
e took down the post after hearing from Clare Locke, which maintained that =
the doctor=E2=80=99s claim was false.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-=
bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">But, in an unexpected twist t=
hat pits Bill against his own law firm, after he took his post down, he spo=
ke extensively with the doctor, who shared her records and emails with him.=
 =E2=80=9CI found her and her story totally credible,=E2=80=9D he subsequen=
tly
tweeted, adding that she was =E2=80=9Ctelling the truth.=E2=80=9D He agreed=
 to cover her expenses in her ongoing legal battle against Clare Locke and =
UnitedHealthcare =E2=80=9Cso that this is a fair fight.=E2=80=9D I have to =
admit, I didn=E2=80=99t have that on my Bill Ackman bingo card.</p></div>
